CME’s TV Nova Extends $17 Million of Credit Line, E15 Reports

-- B y   L e n k a   P o n i k e l s k a
-- 
2011-07-11T08:19:38Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-11/cme-s-tv-nova-extends-17-million-of-credit-line-e15-reports.html
Central European Media Enterprises
Ltd. (CETV) ’s TV Nova channel extended its credit line worth 300
million koruna ($17 million) with Ceska Sporitelna AS,  E15 
reported, citing CME spokeswoman Romana Wyllie.  The credit line, which was unused by TV Nova, expired on
June 30 according to the original agreement, the newspaper said.  TV Nova’s total credit lines from various lenders are worth
1.8 billion koruna, the newspaper added.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Lenka Ponikelska in Prague 
